  "title": "Site Engineering (Architectural Works)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and manage construction site operations to deliver projects on schedule, within budget, and to the highest quality standards, ensuring efficient resource utilization and productivity improvements.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Establish and maintain site control systems to monitor and ensure work schedules, costs, and labor resources align with budgetary targets</li><li>Plan and manage assigned construction projects to achieve timely completion with superior quality outcomes</li><li>Organize and coordinate manpower deployment and delivery schedules to optimize site productivity</li><li>Plan and manage materials and resource allocation to reduce waste and minimize float time on site</li><li>Utilize AutoCAD 2D drawings and MS Office tools to support project planning and documentation</li><li>Apply analytical and operational skills to identify and resolve site challenges, enhancing overall project efficiency</li><li>Lead and communicate effectively with site teams to foster collaboration and maintain high performance standards</li><li>Demonstrate autonomy, reliability, and a target-oriented approach to meet project goals and deadlines</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Architecture or related qualification.</li><li>Proficient command of written and spoken English</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficiency in AutoCAD 2D drawings and MS Office applications</li><li>Strong interpersonal and leadership skills</li><li>Analytical and operational problem-solving abilities</li><li>Self-motivated, career-minded, and responsible work ethic</li></ul>",
